Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - This paper proposes a neuromorphic accelerator architecture for spiking neural networks, which falls under the domain of neural computing. 
2. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper proposes a hardware architecture for the neuromorphic accelerator, which falls under the domain of hardware architecture. 
3. cs.ET (Embedded Systems) - The paper focuses on on-device AI and energy-efficient deep neural networks, which are relevant to embedded systems. 
4. cs.EM (Emerging Technologies) - The paper proposes a new architecture for spiking neural networks, which can be considered an emerging technology. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the communication and computation aspects of the proposed architecture, which can be considered relevant to systems and control.
